subject: Football
lead_paragraph: Kansas State Coach Ron Prince will not return for the 2009 season, pushed out after failing to rebuild the Wildcats into a Big 12 contender. Kansas State Athletic Director Bill Krause fired Prince, effective at the end of the season, only three months after signing him to a five-year contract. Prince took over for Bill Snyder in 2006. He could not match Snyder’s success, going 16-18 in two and a half seasons. ¶Ball State quarterback Nate Davis threw for four touchdowns and ran for another Wednesday as the 16th-ranked Cardinals routed Northern Illinois, 45-14, to remain undefeated and alive in the chase for a Bowl Championship Series berth. MiQuale Lewis topped 100 yards rushing for the ninth straight game for Ball State (9-0, 5-0 Mid-American), which produced eight plays of 25 yards or more. Northern Illinois (5-4, 4-2) allowed nearly six times its average of 8.2 points. ballstate (AP).
